VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)(FileUpload|MultipartFile|CommonsMultipartFile)\s*\(.*\)|\bPart\s*\(.*\)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:getContentType|getOriginalFilename|getSize|allowedTypes|allowedExtensions|maximumSize|validate|sanitize
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects potential unvalidated file uploads in Java applications, which can lead to security vulnerabilities such as remote code execution or denial of service.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for File Upload Functionality.
